cs.SI, cs.SD, cs.CY, cs.IR, cs.SOC

Reasoning: 
1. cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) - The paper focuses on analyzing the structure of the World Wide Web from an audience-centric perspective, which involves studying the relationships between websites based on shared audience traffic. This falls under the purview of social and information networks.
2. cs.SD (Software Engineering) - The paper may also be relevant to software engineering, as it involves constructing network maps and analyzing the structure of the Web using different approaches.
3. cs.CY (Computers and Society) - The paper touches upon cultural factors that may influence the structure of the Web, which is a topic that falls under the domain of computers and society.
4. cs.IR (Information Retrieval) - The paper may also be relevant to information retrieval, as it involves analyzing the relationships between websites based on audience traffic, which is a form of information retrieval.
5. cs.SOC (Social and Behavioral Sciences) - The paper may also be relevant to social and behavioral sciences, as it involves studying the behavior of Web users and how this influences the structure of the Web.
